target.comment:
1. National Strategy for Statistical Development (NSDS) updated; 
2. GamInfo updated and 2014 data available;
3. National DHS and CWIQ data published; 
4. Growth drivers report published and disseminated;
5. Updated CountrySTAT  and media sensitization

actual.comment:
1. NSDS formulation is currently ongoing for 11 Sectors (MoFEA, CBG, MoTRIE, GTB, MoHSW, MoI, MoBSE, MoHERST, GBoS, MoA and Ministry of Works) and a draft consolidated report after the workshop produced;
2. Final reports of DHS, CWIQ and the growth drivers and its impact on poverty and inequality are available to provide the latest national data on demography, health and core warfare indicators. 
3. A two day stakeholders’ forum (data producers and users) was organized with 43 participants from various sectors. The purpose of the forum is to have a dialogue to identify data needs, gaps and challenges and to sensitize the users on data availability;
4. 2 days Step-Down Training on CountrySTAT conducted and the training provided a broad framework for development of individual capacity on computer, methods of data collection, validation, verification and uploading.
5. Antivirus software packed was installed to secure the Country Stat database.

