actual.comment:
1. National Human Development Report (NHDR) on youths and employment reviewed and updated;
2. Institutional capacity of Ministry of Youths and Sports (MOYS) improved as a result of the development of revised MOYS policy/Strategic Development Plan 2010 – 2014, revised National Youth Council Act 2000 and revised NYSS policy documents;
3. MDG status report has been launched in the 7 regions of the country, with 500 participants sensitized on the findings of the MDG status report 2014; 
4. 5 days training was conducted and has improved 50 MDA capacity on Result-Based Management and planning techniques.
5. The M&E online system has been developed. 6 days training was conducted and capacities of 7 Administrators and 40 users have been strengthened on General Information Monitoring and Evaluation System. 
6. 7 days training on M&E conducted for 25 MDA’s to strengthen their capacities on Monitoring and Evaluation; 
7. The Documentation Center of PAU is equipped with necessary equipment and networking of computers completed with the development of web-based system. 
8. Two trainings for 5 days each were conducted on aid coordination for 35 project staff and 25 aid coordination taskforce members and workshop report produced; 
9. A day long Development Forum with the Theme “Closing the Gender Gap: The realities in The Gambia”, coordinated by the Office of the Vice President has been conducted successfully;
10. Citizens Budget and Manual finalized and printed. 
11. The Kuntaur Area Council strategic plan and profile were developed, printed and launched.  200 participants from various institutions attended the launching in Janjanbureh.  Resources and capacity gaps were identified from the strategic plan which gave a clear vision and development direction for the council. 
